)..........................4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1399,1284,1381]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
– Face with only a trace of a tubercle, almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[896,998,1319,1346]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[269,1332,267,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[253,1335,253,1840]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 4. A, C–D. Melanostoma polynesiotes Mengual &amp; Ramage sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (ZFMK- DIP-00019707). A. Lateral view. C. Lateral view. D. Head, lateral view. B, E. Ornidia obesa (Fabricius, 1775), ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019747). B. Dorsal view. E. Frontal view. F. Syritta aenigmatopatria Hardy, 1964, ♀ (ZFMK-DIP-00019739), frontal view. G. Palpada vinetorum (Fabricius, 1798), ♀ (ZFMK- DIP-00019738), frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3814067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3814067/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs 4D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1015,1053,1320,1346]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="27.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[218,1370,265,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[203,1383,250,1871]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Fig. 7. A, C, E. Melanostoma fasciatum (Macquart, 1850), ♂ (AM_K407062). A. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. E. Head and thorax, lateral view. B, D. Melanostoma univittatum (Wiedemann, 1824), ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019737). B. Dorsal view. D. Lateral view. F. Melanostoma apicale Bigot, 1884, ♀ (ZFMK-DIP-00019781), lateral view. Scale bars: A–D, F = 1 mm; E = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3814073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3814073/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">7D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1070,1110,1320,1346]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="29.[189,232,1718,1744]" captionTargetBox="[314,1276,267,1683]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[303,1284,246,1693]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Fig. 9. A–B. Melanostoma apicale Bigot, 1884, ♂ (from Ôhara &amp; Kusigemati 1985, as M. univittatum (Wiedemann, 1824)). A. Head, lateral view. B. Abdomen, dorsal view. C. Melanostoma mellinum (Linnaeus, 1758), ♂, metasternum, ventral view (from Vockeroth &amp; Thompson 1987; mtst = metasternum, cx3 = metacoxa). D–F. Melanostoma polynesiotes Mengual &amp; Ramage sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019707), genitalia. D. Epandrium with surstylus and cercus, lateral view. E. Hypandrium, lateral view. F. Hypandrium, ventral view. G–H. M. apicale Bigot, 1884, ♂, genitalia, lateral view (from Ôhara &amp; Kusigemati 1985, as M. univittatum (Wiedemann, 1824)). G. Epandrium with surstylus and cercus. H. Hypandrium. I. Melanostoma univittatum (Wiedemann, 1824), ♂ (ZFMK- DIP-00019737), surstylus and part of epandrium and cercus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3814077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3814077/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">9A</figureCitation>
); male genitalia greatly enlarged, usually visible externally (
<figureCitation box="[673,774,1354,1381]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[279,1311,268,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[264,1323,251,1804]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 6. A. Ischiodon scutellaris (Fabricius, 1805), ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019713), metacoxa and metatrochanter. Arrow indicates the ventral spine-like process. B. Simosyrphus grandicornis (Macquart, 1842), ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019736), metacoxa and metatrochanter. C–E. Allograpta jacqui Mengual &amp; Ramage sp. nov., holotype ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00026906). C. Lateral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Frontal view. F–G. Melanostoma polynesiotes Mengual &amp; Ramage sp. nov., paratype, ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00026902). F. Dorsolateral view. G. Lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3814071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3814071/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs 6G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[790,866,1355,1381]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="27.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[218,1370,265,1861]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[203,1383,250,1871]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Fig. 7. A, C, E. Melanostoma fasciatum (Macquart, 1850), ♂ (AM_K407062). A. Dorsal view. C. Lateral view. E. Head and thorax, lateral view. B, D. Melanostoma univittatum (Wiedemann, 1824), ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019737). B. Dorsal view. D. Lateral view. F. Melanostoma apicale Bigot, 1884, ♀ (ZFMK-DIP-00019781), lateral view. Scale bars: A–D, F = 1 mm; E = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3814073" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3814073/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">7B, D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[882,917,1355,1381]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="29.[189,232,1718,1744]" captionTargetBox="[314,1276,267,1683]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[303,1284,246,1693]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Fig. 9. A–B. Melanostoma apicale Bigot, 1884, ♂ (from Ôhara &amp; Kusigemati 1985, as M. univittatum (Wiedemann, 1824)). A. Head, lateral view. B. Abdomen, dorsal view. C. Melanostoma mellinum (Linnaeus, 1758), ♂, metasternum, ventral view (from Vockeroth &amp; Thompson 1987; mtst = metasternum, cx3 = metacoxa). D–F. Melanostoma polynesiotes Mengual &amp; Ramage sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019707), genitalia. D. Epandrium with surstylus and cercus, lateral view. E. Hypandrium, lateral view. F. Hypandrium, ventral view. G–H. M. apicale Bigot, 1884, ♂, genitalia, lateral view (from Ôhara &amp; Kusigemati 1985, as M. univittatum (Wiedemann, 1824)). G. Epandrium with surstylus and cercus. H. Hypandrium. I. Melanostoma univittatum (Wiedemann, 1824), ♂ (ZFMK- DIP-00019737), surstylus and part of epandrium and cercus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3814077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3814077/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">9B</figureCitation>
).............................................................2
