<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1399,1427,1701]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
2. Abdominal terga entirely black (
<figureCitation box="[643,747,1428,1454]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[269,1332,267,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[253,1335,253,1840]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 4. A, C–D. Melanostoma polynesiotes Mengual &amp; Ramage sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (ZFMK- DIP-00019707). A. Lateral view. C. Lateral view. D. Head, lateral view. B, E. Ornidia obesa (Fabricius, 1775), ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019747). B. Dorsal view. E. Frontal view. F. Syritta aenigmatopatria Hardy, 1964, ♀ (ZFMK-DIP-00019739), frontal view. G. Palpada vinetorum (Fabricius, 1798), ♀ (ZFMK- DIP-00019738), frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3814067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3814067/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs 4A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[766,780,1427,1454]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[279,1311,268,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[264,1323,251,1804]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 6. A. Ischiodon scutellaris (Fabricius, 1805), ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019713), metacoxa and metatrochanter. Arrow indicates the ventral spine-like process. B. Simosyrphus grandicornis (Macquart, 1842), ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019736), metacoxa and metatrochanter. C–E. Allograpta jacqui Mengual &amp; Ramage sp. nov., holotype ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00026906). C. Lateral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Frontal view. F–G. Melanostoma polynesiotes Mengual &amp; Ramage sp. nov., paratype, ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00026902). F. Dorsolateral view. G. Lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3814071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3814071/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">6</figureCitation>
F–G); legs partly black in both male and female (
<figureCitation box="[243,350,1463,1489]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1860,1886]" captionTargetBox="[269,1332,267,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[253,1335,253,1840]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 4. A, C–D. Melanostoma polynesiotes Mengual &amp; Ramage sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (ZFMK- DIP-00019707). A. Lateral view. C. Lateral view. D. Head, lateral view. B, E. Ornidia obesa (Fabricius, 1775), ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019747). B. Dorsal view. E. Frontal view. F. Syritta aenigmatopatria Hardy, 1964, ♀ (ZFMK-DIP-00019739), frontal view. G. Palpada vinetorum (Fabricius, 1798), ♀ (ZFMK- DIP-00019738), frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3814067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3814067/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs 4C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[373,387,1463,1490]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[189,232,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[279,1311,268,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[264,1323,251,1804]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 6. A. Ischiodon scutellaris (Fabricius, 1805), ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019713), metacoxa and metatrochanter. Arrow indicates the ventral spine-like process. B. Simosyrphus grandicornis (Macquart, 1842), ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019736), metacoxa and metatrochanter. C–E. Allograpta jacqui Mengual &amp; Ramage sp. nov., holotype ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00026906). C. Lateral view. D. Dorsal view. E. Frontal view. F–G. Melanostoma polynesiotes Mengual &amp; Ramage sp. nov., paratype, ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00026902). F. Dorsolateral view. G. Lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3814071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3814071/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">6</figureCitation>
F–G). Male genitalia: surstylus curved towards dorsal part (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1281,1463,1489]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="29.[189,232,1718,1744]" captionTargetBox="[314,1276,267,1683]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[303,1284,246,1693]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Fig. 9. A–B. Melanostoma apicale Bigot, 1884, ♂ (from Ôhara &amp; Kusigemati 1985, as M. univittatum (Wiedemann, 1824)). A. Head, lateral view. B. Abdomen, dorsal view. C. Melanostoma mellinum (Linnaeus, 1758), ♂, metasternum, ventral view (from Vockeroth &amp; Thompson 1987; mtst = metasternum, cx3 = metacoxa). D–F. Melanostoma polynesiotes Mengual &amp; Ramage sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (ZFMK-DIP-00019707), genitalia. D. Epandrium with surstylus and cercus, lateral view. E. Hypandrium, lateral view. F. Hypandrium, ventral view. G–H. M. apicale Bigot, 1884, ♂, genitalia, lateral view (from Ôhara &amp; Kusigemati 1985, as M. univittatum (Wiedemann, 1824)). G. Epandrium with surstylus and cercus. H. Hypandrium. I. Melanostoma univittatum (Wiedemann, 1824), ♂ (ZFMK- DIP-00019737), surstylus and part of epandrium and cercus, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3814077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3814077/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
) (
<collectingCountry name="French Polynesia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">French Polynesia</collectingCountry>
) ................................................................................................... 
